1
00:00:05,724 --> 00:00:08,757
We’re addicted to … 
because we live in the world

2
00:00:08,757 --> 00:00:11,208
of time and space
and measurement,

3
00:00:11,208 --> 00:00:12,768
we’re always 
measuring things—

4
00:00:12,768 --> 00:00:14,649
this is that far from here,

5
00:00:14,649 --> 00:00:17,851
and Thailand is this far
from India or Russia.

6
00:00:18,204 --> 00:00:21,256
[“A Map of Reality”]

7
00:00:21,671 --> 00:00:24,682
We think like that, so we hear,
“Oh, Ayodhyā’s here,

8
00:00:24,682 --> 00:00:27,246
and Vaikuṇṭha’s over there,
and Goloka ….”

9
00:00:27,246 --> 00:00:29,846
We can’t think of it
in terms of time and space;

10
00:00:29,846 --> 00:00:33,408
we need to think of it 
in terms of conscious development

11
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:35,568
and dedicating conscious tendency—

12
00:00:35,568 --> 00:00:43,981
that’s what separates spiritual regions
from one another:

13
00:00:43,981 --> 00:00:50,328
a conscious development
of dedicating tendency,

14
00:00:50,405 --> 00:00:59,981
not some topographical, 
cartographic type representation of it

15
00:00:59,981 --> 00:01:02,686
which an artist is likely to do
if they make a painting—

16
00:01:02,686 --> 00:01:05,009
you know, put Goloka here,
and then the Vaikuṇṭha world,

17
00:01:05,009 --> 00:01:07,817
and then …, like that.
But we’re told,

18
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:10,424
chintāmaṇiś charaṇa-bhūṣaṇam aṅganānāṁ:

19
00:01:10,424 --> 00:01:15,688
the whole Vaikuṇṭha world is accommodated
in an atom of Goloka.

20
00:01:15,688 --> 00:01:19,044
So you have to really change
your thinking about that,

21
00:01:19,168 --> 00:01:24,464
which means to come under the influence
of revealed truth;

22
00:01:24,526 --> 00:01:33,208
give way to the time, 
space, measurement,

23
00:01:33,208 --> 00:01:35,886
consideration that we have
of the limited world.

24
00:01:35,886 --> 00:01:39,518
If we’re going to discuss
the unlimited world,

25
00:01:39,518 --> 00:01:42,559
that needs to be suppressed,

26
00:01:42,606 --> 00:01:45,807
therefore it’s called
the adhokṣaja realm.

27
00:01:45,807 --> 00:01:48,887
There are those who think that
by suppressing sense experience

28
00:01:48,887 --> 00:01:52,542
you’ll experience the higher;

29
00:01:52,543 --> 00:01:56,808
that can only take you to a generic,
neutral position.

30
00:01:56,808 --> 00:02:00,910
But when the higher plane comes down,
then, adhokṣaja:

31
00:02:00,910 --> 00:02:04,287
automatically 
the lower experience

32
00:02:04,287 --> 00:02:06,886
is suppressed 
in the presence of that,

33
00:02:06,886 --> 00:02:10,758
so there’s total immersion
in that domain.

